    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Yordan Alvarez** providing the clear anchor; his 77.33 projection against Andre Pallante is our highest mark, bolstered by his elite .393 xwOBA and favorable lineup placement. Following him, **Hyeseong Kim** (70.16) and **Colt Keith** (68.51) emerge as high-upside plays. **Hyeseong Kim** is particularly interesting today; while his batting order is projected lower, he faces a slower pitcher delivery that maximizes his stolen base potential, a critical factor for our 5x5 Roto needs. Similarly, **Carson Benge** maintains a strong 67.06 score, benefiting significantly from the leadoff spot and a positive platoon edge against Taillon. We are closely monitoring the lineup postings for **Dillon Dingler**, **Gary Sanchez**, and **Victor Scott II**; while their scores are currently weighted by assumed positions, any shift in their batting order could necessitate immediate lineup adjustments.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench involved **Jerar Encarnacion**, whose 46.11 efficiency score fell just outside our target starting threshold. While he offers some value, the optimizer prioritized the specific speed and platoon advantages provided by our outfield trio, particularly **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (64.51), whose dynamic platoon outlook and aggressive base-running environment against a slow-moving pitcher outpaced **Jerar Encarnacion**. We have also benched **Caleb Durbin** (42.48) and **Josh Smith** (40.33); **Caleb Durbin** faced the steepest hurdle today, as the matchup against a high-tier arm like Tarik Skubal suppressed his efficiency to levels below our roster floor. We continue to hold **Zac Veen** in the minors, awaiting an active roster promotion to provide the high-octane speed profile we require. Caution is advised with **Trea Turner** and **Kyle Schwarber**, both of whom are facing the elite Chris Sale; while their talent floor keeps them in the lineup, their scores are significantly depressed by Sale\u2019s sub-3.00 xERA, making them the most volatile assets on our roster for today\u2019s matchups.",
